Retention Period of Personal Location Information
Targeted advertising service
Provision of targeted advertising services using personal location information
Retention period necessary to provide services to users
Geotagging service
Geotagging of photo taken at landmarks, etc.
Grounds for and retention period ofdata verifying use and provision of personal location information
We record and retain data verifying use and provision of location information pursuant to Article 16, Paragraph (2)
          of the Act on Protection and Use of Location Information (the “Location Information Act”) for at least 6
          months.
Procedures and methods for destruction ofpersonal location information
We take measures to ensure complete destruction of personal location information in an irrevocable manner
          when the purpose of processing personal location information is achieved.  Electronic files are destroyed by
          technical means that cannot be restored or reproduced, and printouts are destroyed by shredding or incinerating.
Matters concerning provision of personal location information to a third party
and notification
                  thereof
;
We will not provide personal location information to any third party without obtaining prior consent from
          you. If we provide your personal location information to a third party designated by you, we will notify
          you of the designated recipient’s name, date and time of the provision, and purpose of
          the provision at the time of each provision without delay.
We will provide personal location information only in the following cases (i) where you consent to the
          provision of personal location information for the purpose of using the services provided by an external
          partner; (ii) where we are obligated to provide your personal location information pursuant to
          applicable laws and regulations; or (iii) where there is an imminent risk to your life or safety is
          identified and it is necessary to provide your personal location information to resolve such risk.
Rights and duties of legal guardians and the method of exercising such rights and duties
Where a legal guardian of user who falls under any of the following categories consents to the use or
          provision of personal location information for the protection of such user's life or body, it will be deemed
          that the user has given consent thereto.
A person under adult guardianship
A person with a mental disability defined in Article 2 (2) 2 of the Act on Welfare of Persons with Disabilities,
              who is classified as a person with a severe disability defined in subparagraph 2 of Article 2 of the Act on the
              Employment Promotion and Vocational Rehabilitation of Persons with Disabilities (limited to those registered as
              disabled persons under Article 32 of the Act on Welfare of Persons with Disabilities);
A legal guardian who intends to consent to the use or provision of personal location information for the
          protection of such user’s life or body shall submit a written consent to us, together with a document
          evidencing his/her legal guardian status.
After giving consents to the use or provision of such user’s personal location information, the legal
          guardian can exercise all of the rights of the personal location information on behalf of the user under
          the Location Information Act.
Name, contact information such as telephone number of location management officer or department in charge of
              protecting personal location information and handling complaints.
